name: Fancy Franks
author: Marie
summary: This easy and cheap recipe dresses up hot dogs--perfect for kids, get-togethers, and picnics. As long as you keep an eye on them, these also cook up perfectly under a broiler.
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
Spray a baking sheet with non-stick cooking spray
Being careful not to slice them into two separate pieces, make a lengthwise slit from the top of every hot dog to the bottom
Spread open the franks, then place them side by side flat side-up on the baking sheet
Season each hot dog with a pinch of celery salt, then put a slice of cheese on top of each frank
Spread a thin layer of barbeque sauce over each piece of cheese
Bake until cheese is slightly browned on edges, about 10 minutes
